vernac_cmds: Definition has_n_elements (n : Nat) (A : Setoid) := exists v : seq n A, full A =' seq_set v in _ /\ distinct v.

generalize H0; generalize H1; clear H1 H0; intros H0 H1.

apply Trans with (subtype_elt (Map_to_equal_subsets H1 x j)); auto with algebra.
Lemma n_element_subset_sequence : forall (A : Setoid) (n : Nat) (B : part_set A), has_n_elements n B -> exists v : seq n A, B =' seq_set v in _ /\ distinct v.
generalize (H (Build_subtype H0)); clear H; intros (p, q); generalize (p I); clear p q; intro.
apply in_part_comp_l with (subtype_elt (x x0)); auto with algebra.

Lemma has_zero_elements_then_empty : forall (A : Setoid) (B : part_set A), has_n_elements 0 B -> B =' empty A in _.

Lemma empty_then_has_zero_elements : forall (A : Setoid) (B : part_set A), B =' empty A in _ -> has_n_elements 0 B.

Lemma full_preserves_has_n_elements : forall (A : Setoid) (n : Nat), has_n_elements n A -> has_n_elements n (full A).
